    "Similarly, in predicting the pharmacodynamic properties of dezocine, camostat, ropivacaine, montelukast, and silodosin, GPT-4 demonstrated better performance in specific details than GPT-3.5.With regard to other pharmacological properties of drugs, such as pharmacodynamics and toxicity, GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 demonstrated similar and excellent performance, achieving accuracy rates of 85.00 ± 3.27% and 95.00 ± 0.00%, respectively.",
